\cf2 \cb3 GR2: Links to the our terms and conditions URL to be displayed\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\fs32 \cf2 \cb3 Provide a link to our terms and conditions within your site's own terms and conditions text or directly link to the terms from your booking page. These terms detail the policies that govern the booking. Place the following link in an easy-to-find location, using the link wording "Supplier Terms & Conditions".\cb1 \
\cb3 Versions of the terms and conditions in every language we support are available from this\'a0{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://support.expediapartnersolutions.com/hc/en-us/articles/360015079020-Rapid-Terms-Conditions?brand_id=181541"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 \ul \ulc4 \strokec4 Rapid API terms and conditions page}}.\cb1 \
\cb3 Example:\cb1 \
\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\fs24 \cf2 {{\NeXTGraphic New-B2B-LRs-Terms-and-Conditions.jpeg \width9660 \height4560 \appleattachmentpadding0 \appleembedtype0 \appleaqc
}洞\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\fs32 \cf2 \cb3 GR4: Proper use and display of credit card regulations when Expedia Group is the Merchant of Record (MoR)\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\fs24 \cf2 \cb3 Where you obtain, use, transmit, store or process traveler's cardholder data, you must comply with the Payment Card Industry (PCI) Data Security Standard as issued by the PCI Security Standards Council. A complete reference for these regulations is available at the official\'a0{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://www.pcisecuritystandards.org/"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 \ul \ulc4 \strokec4 PCI Security Standards Council}}\'a0website.\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\fs32 \cf2 \cb3 GR5: Evidence of PCI compliance supplied for either property collect or when Expedia Group is the MoR (applicable partners only)\cb1 \
\cb3 Whether Expedia Group is the MoR or the property is the MoR, an Attestation of Compliance (AOC) must be supplied as evidence of PCI compliance.\cb1 \
\cb3 You can find advice regarding PCI compliance on the official\'a0{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://www.pcisecuritystandards.org/"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 \ul \ulc4 \strokec4 PCI Security Standards Council}}\'a0website.\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

