\fs32 \cb3 BP1: SSL encryption present for personal data\cb1 \
\cb3 When sending or transmitting personal data, you must use SSL encryption to secure connections between client browsers/applications and your site, as well as the network communications with dependent systems. Personal data includes guest names, phone numbers or emails, payment card details, and booking/itinerary receipts and confirmation pages. Stop or redirect the connection when it is not secured.\cb1 \
\cb3 BP2: Check-in and special instructions displayed\cb1 \
\cb3 The contents of the\'a0
\f1\fs20\fsmilli10200 \cb8 checkin
\f0\fs32 \cb3 ,\'a0
