\cf2 \cb3 BP7: Child ages are reiterated (if applicable)\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\fs32 \cf2 \cb3 If your integration permits child travelers and the traveler specified child travelers for their room selection, you must clearly confirm the number of child travelers and their ages on your booking pages. This information is provided via the\'a0
\f1\fs20\fsmilli10200 \cb8 child_ages
\f0\fs32 \cb3 \'a0object.\cb1 \
\cb3 BP8: Statement of when payment will be taken from the end traveler (for property collect or when Expedia Group is the MoR)\cb1 \
\cb3 If Expeda Group is the MoR, state that the credit card provided will be charged immediately for the full amount of the reservation.\cb1 \
\cb3 If Property Collect, state that the credit card provided will be charged by the property at check-in or check-out. If the property is serving a non-refundable post-pay rate, instead indicate that the traveler could be charged by the property shortly after completing the booking.\cb1 \
\cb3 BP9: Compliant with SCA regulation\cb1 \
\cb3 Regulatory agencies and card networks are introducing new requirements to strengthen security for online payments and protect consumers from fraud. Many of these regulations have included the requirement to use strong customer authentication (SCA) for online payments.\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://developers.expediagroup.com/rapid/lodging/booking/sca-regulation"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 \cb3 \ul \ulc4 \strokec4 Learn more about strong customer authentication (SCA)}}\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \cb3 BP10: Payment processing location displayed on check-out pages when Expedia Group is MoR\cb1 \
\cb3 Where Expedia Group is the MoR, the country where the payment will be processed must be displayed in a prominent place on the check-out page. The phrase\'a0
\f2\i \'93This payment will be processed in\'94
\f0\i0 \'a0must be inserted before the country name.\cb1 \
\cb3 Use the payment options function of the Shopping API to retrieve this information.\cb1 \
\cb3 Example API request for payment options:\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f1\fs20\fsmilli10200 \cf2 \cb8 https://api.ean.com/<payment-options link from previous availability request>
\f0\fs32 \cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
