\fs28 \cf2 \cb3 Confirmation email/voucher\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\fs24 \cf2 \

\fs32 \cb3 If you will provide a hosted voucher within a mobile application, please continue to follow the requirements below.\cb1 \
\cb3 ER1: Itinerary IDs displayed properly\cb1 \
\cb3 CDS only\cb1 \
\cb3 If your integration will provide our\'a0
\f1\fs20\fsmilli10200 \cb8 itinerary_id
\f0\fs32 \cb3 \'a0directly to the traveler, you must clearly display this number on your confirmation email.\cb1 \
\cb3 If applicable, you must provide evidence that your agents have access to the our original itinerary IDs should they require assistance from our customer support.\cb1 \
\cb3 A2A\cb1 \
\cb3 Your agents should have access to their original itinerary IDs should they require assistance from our customer support.\cb1 \
\cb3 ER2: Customer support clearly displayed, including links to online customer service tools\cb1 \
\cb3 Clearly display your customer support channels within the booking flow or within the confirmation email e.g. telephone number or live chat. If our agents will be providing direct support to travelers, display the our support number in your booking flow.\cb1 \
\cb3 ER3: Bed type descriptions present on each room\cb1 \
\cb3 Confirm the traveler-requested bed type in your confirmation email/voucher and display messaging to the traveler that choices between multiple bed types for the same room are requests only and may not be honored at the hotel if availability does not permit.\cb1 \
\cb3 Display the values contained in the configuration array to describe the traveler's bed choice(s).\cb1 \
\cb3 ER4: Check-in and special instructions displayed\cb1 \
\cb3 The contents of the\'a0
\f1\fs20\fsmilli10200 \cb8 checkin
\f0\fs32 \cb3 ,\'a0
\f1\fs20\fsmilli10200 \cb8 checkout
\f0\fs32 \cb3 ,\'a0
\f1\fs20\fsmilli10200 \cb8 fees
\f0\fs32 \cb3 , and\'a0
\f1\fs20\fsmilli10200 \cb8 policies
\f0\fs32 \cb3 \'a0objects must be displayed for each room as returned in the property content definition. This information must be displayed on your availability page to ensure the traveler is aware of any potential fees at check-in or special access instructions.\cb1 \
\cb3 The special check-in field may include information critical for check-in that is not included in the\'a0
\f1\fs20\fsmilli10200 \cb8 checkin
\f0\fs32 \cb3 \'a0object's instructions field, such as a requirement to notify the property of expected arrival time, check-in at a different location from the guest building, or an alert to expect special check-in instructions from the property via email.\cb1 \
\cb3 Make sure to display both the\'a0
\f1\fs20\fsmilli10200 \cb8 instructions
\f0\fs32 \cb3 \'a0and\'a0
\f1\fs20\fsmilli10200 \cb8 special_instructions
\f0\fs32 \cb3 \'a0to the traveler within the same area.\cb1 \
\cb3 ER5: Charges due separately at the property displayed within the price breakdown\cb1 \
\cb3 When charges are returned in the fees array, display each value separately as a charge due at the property (check-in or check-out). These charges are collected directly by the property (not us or local government) and are not part of standard tax recovery charges.\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\fs28 \cf2 \cb3 Technical and sanctions requirements\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\fs24 \cf2 \

\fs32 \cb3 TR1: Provide unique affiliate reference ID with each booking request\cb1 \
\cb3 For every booking request you must use the\'a0
\f1\fs20\fsmilli10200 \cb8 affiliate_reference_id
\f0\fs32 \cb3 \'a0element with the intent of:\cb1 \
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\partightenfactor0
\ls7\ilvl0
\fs24 \cf2 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 \uc0\u8232 \cb3 Your own tracking.\cb1 \uc0\u8232 \u8232 \cb3 Preventing duplicate bookings/duplicate charges from multiple form submissions.\cb1 \uc0\u8232 \u8232 \cb3 Checking our systems for an itinerary if the reservation timed out or returned an empty result due to upstream timeouts.
\fs32 \cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \cb3 Example:\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f1\fs20\fsmilli10200 \cf3 \cb9 \strokec3 \{\
  \cf10 \strokec10 "affiliate_reference_id"\cf3 \strokec3 : \cf10 \strokec10 "Launch_Requirement_TR1"\cf3 \strokec3  ,\
 \cf10 \strokec10 "hold"\cf3 \strokec3 : \cf11 \strokec11 false\cf3 \strokec3 ,\
 \cf10 \strokec10 "email"\cf3 \strokec3 : \cf10 \strokec10 "TR4@Launch.Requirement"\cf3 \strokec3 ,\
 \cf10 \strokec10 "phone"\cf3 \strokec3 : \{\
    \cf10 \strokec10 "country_code"\cf3 \strokec3 : \cf10 \strokec10 "Launch_Requirement_TR5b"\cf3 \strokec3 ,\
    \cf10 \strokec10 "number"\cf3 \strokec3 : \cf10 \strokec10 "Launch_Requirement_TR5b"\cf3 \strokec3 ,\
    \cf10 \strokec10 "area_code"\cf3 \strokec3 : \cf10 \strokec10 "Launch_Requirement_TR5b"\cf3 \strokec3 \
 \},\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf10 \strokec10 "rooms"\cf3 \strokec3 : [\
 \{\
    \cf10 \strokec10 "given_name"\cf3 \strokec3 : \cf10 \strokec10 "John_Launch_Requirement_TR5a"\cf3 \strokec3 ,\
    \cf10 \strokec10 "family_name"\cf3 \strokec3 : \cf10 \strokec10 "Doe_Launch_Requirement_TR5a,\
    "\cf3 \strokec3 smoking\cf10 \strokec10 ": false,\
 \},\
 \{\
    "\cf3 \strokec3 given_name\cf10 \strokec10 ": "\cf3 \strokec3 David_Launch_Requirement_TR5a\cf10 \strokec10 ",\
