\fs32 \cf2 \cb3 \strokec2 TR4: Provide the traveler email address or monitored email mailbox\cb1 \
\cb3 The email element of each itinerary must contain the traveler email address or the mailbox your integration monitors for confirmation email handling. This is required for cases of booking disputes or troubleshooting.\cb1 \
\cb3 TR5: Provide accurate traveler information\cb1 \
\cb3 A) Traveler name\cb1 \
\cb3 Bookings must always be submitted with the name of the actual travelers staying in each booked room. This means that in your booking request body the values for\'a0
\f1\fs20\fsmilli10200 \cb8 given_name
\f0\fs32 \cb3 \'a0and\'a0
\f1\fs20\fsmilli10200 \cb8 family_name
\f0\fs32 \cb3 \'a0within the rooms object must match the first and last name of the main guest checking in for each room.\cb1 \
\cb3 B) Traveler phone number\cb1 \
\cb3 The booking must include a viable contact number for the traveler. Include this number in your booking request's phone field of each itinerary. Expedia Group will not contact the traveler if the your agents provide direct support to travelers.\cb1 \
\cb3 TR6: Provide multi-room booking information\cb1 \
\cb3 If multi-room bookings are supported, provide the API request and response logs for a test booking which shows each room has been booked and cancelled.\cb1 \
\cb3 Each room that is booked will create a separate Confirmation ID, which allows the rooms to be cancelled separately. To cancel all rooms, complete a cancellation call for every confirmation ID within the itinerary.\cb1 \
\cb3 Expedia Group do not directly offer group bookings of more than 8 rooms through our API or template. Your account manager can advise you if you need to book more than 8 rooms.\cb1 \
\cb3 TR7: Review error handling recommendations\cb1 \
\cb3 Please confirm you have reviewed our\'a0{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://developers.expediagroup.com/rapid/resources/handle-booking-reqs-lodging"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 \ul \ulc4 \strokec4 error handling recommendations}}\'a0and implemented logic to handle them.\cb1 \

